This has been my favorite place to eat lunch since the opening. The food is really fresh and every menu item is tasty, feels really healthy and well balanced in terms of nutritional value (it would be helpful to see calories per item). The place is clean and cozy and the staff has always been kind and cooperative. Thanks.

I was taken aback by the young lady at the counter this afternoon. I was trying to order some soup and her attitude was unexpected. I asked her the differences between the soup options and she responded "the ingredients." I asked if she could explain the difference between two specific options (out of three), and she proceeded to silently open and push a menu in front of me. At that point I was really biting my tongue because I was unsure why she was having a snarky attitude with me. I finally asked her what her favorite was and moved on. I wasn't impressed with the purchase. I'm sure the other items on the menu are refreshing but I felt the Ginger Sesame Soup was not worth $9. Was happy with the gentleman who ended up delivering my order at the counter and created a more welcoming atmosphere. However, I won't be returning.

Honestly, this is the only restaurant I've ever been to that I feel like is as healthy as the stuff I'd make at home.  Their kale chips are extra delicious, I love the cauliflower wrap, and staff is nice.  Just be warned that an organic vegan restaurant that centers around whole foods isn't cheap, and if you need a weird customization for your order they might not get it every time.  (I have a garlic issue and request things without the garlic cashew sauce, and sometimes they leave out the cashew cheese too because they assume the nuts are the problem.)

Incredibly clean and modern space right on Connecticut Ave. Extensive (and expensive) menu, but works for the area and what they sell. The açaí bowl was remarkable. Fresh & delicious which is all I wanted. Solid place for breakfast or lunch! Will be back.
